The Store is the central place where the entire state of your application is stored.

It acts as the brain of Redux, managing how state updates and how components access data.

The store is created using the createStore() or (modern way) configureStore() method from Redux Toolkit.

It connects the actions, reducers, and the UI together.

Example:

import { configureStore } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';
import todoReducer from './todoReducer';

const store = configureStore({ reducer: todoReducer });



